efg | 2019-03-03

1 Purpose

The purpose of this notebook is to take a preliminary look at the raw data from 5000 patients in the PhysioNet 2019 challenge, where some had sepsis and some did not.

The focus of this notebook is on the Demographics data (columns 35-40 in the raw files):

Quantity Units Description
Age Years
Gender Female (0) or Male (1)
Unit1 Administrative identifier for ICU unit (MICU)
Unit2 Administrative identifier for ICU unit (SICU)
HospAdmTime Hours Time between hospital admit and ICU admit
ICULOS Hours ICU length-of-stay (hours since ICU admit)

and the outcome (column 41)

  • SepsisLabel. For sepsis patients, SepsisLabel is 1 if \(t \ge t_{sepsis} - 6\) and 0 if \(t < t_{sepsis} - 6\). For non-sepsis patients, SepsisLabel is 0.

2 Background

The data being analyzed is from the Early Prediction of Sepsis from Clinical Data: the PhysioNet/Computing in Cardiology Challenge 2019.

3.1.2 Helper function

Show <- function(data, caption="", bigMark="", ...)
{
  data                                          %>%
  kable("html",
        caption=caption,
        format.args = list(big.mark=bigMark))   %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "bordered", "condensed"),
                position = "left", full_width = FALSE, ...)
}

3.1.4 Create Patient Summary

Verify certain values are constant for a patient

Not shown here, but I verified Age, Gender, Unit1 and Unit2 were constant for each patient.

Shown here is proof that HospAdmTime does not change by patient.

allData              %>%
  group_by(patient)  %>%
  summarize(minHospAdmTime = min(HospAdmTime),
            maxHospAdmTime = max(HospAdmTime))  %>%
  ungroup()          %>%
  filter(minHospAdmTime != maxHospAdmTime)      %>%
  Show()
patient minHospAdmTime maxHospAdmTime

So, lets grab the first value for most quantities, but verify range of ICULOS.

patientSummary <- 
  allData                               %>%
  
  group_by(patient)                     %>%
  summarize(nRecord     = n(),
            Age         = Age[1],
            Gender      = Gender[1],
            Unit1       = Unit1[1],
            Unit2       = Unit2[1],
            HospAdmTime = HospAdmTime[1],
            minICULOS   = min(ICULOS),
            maxICULOS   = max(ICULOS),
            gapICULOS   = max(diff(ICULOS)),
            Sepsis      = max(SepsisLabel),
            FirstSepsisHour = ICULOS[which(SepsisLabel == 1)][1],
            LastSepsisHour  = ICULOS[rev( which(SepsisLabel == 1) )][1],
            Duration        = LastSepsisHour - FirstSepsisHour + 1) %>%
  ungroup()                             %>%
  
  mutate(Gender = recode(Gender,
                         "0" = "Female",
                         "1" = "Male"),
         Sepsis = recode(Sepsis,
                         "0" = "Non-Sepsis",
                         "1" = "Sepsis"))

firstSepsisHourCounts <-
  patientSummary              %>%
  filter(Sepsis == "Sepsis")  %>%
  group_by(FirstSepsisHour)   %>%
  count()                     %>%
  ungroup()

Sepsis reported in first hour for 20.1% of sepsis patients.

firstSepsisHourCounts     %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = FirstSepsisHour, y = n))                        +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill="blue")                     +

4 Discussion

Only about 1.4% of raw records indicate sepsis.

Only about 5.6% of the patients have sepsis.

Sepsis reported in first hour for 20.1% of sepsis patients.
